SafePlay Hub
Description:
SafePlay Hub is a simple user authentication system built with Node.js, Express, and MongoDB. It allows users to register, login, and view their profile with JWT-based authentication.

Features:
User Registration
User Login (with JWT token)
Profile Access (authenticated)
Technologies:
Node.js
Express.js
MongoDB
JWT (JSON Web Token)
bcryptjs (password hashing)
Setup Instructions:
Clone the repository:
bash
Copy
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/safeplay-hub.git
Navigate to the project folder:
bash
Copy
cd safeplay-hub
Install dependencies:
bash
Copy
npm install
Create a .env file and set your MongoDB URI and JWT secret:
bash
Copy
MONGO_URI=<your_mongodb_connection_string>
JWT_SECRET=<your_jwt_secret>
Run the application:
bash
Copy
npm start
API Endpoints:
POST /api/user/register: Register a new user
Request body:

json
Copy
{ "name": "User", "email": "email@example.com", "password": "password123" }
POST /api/user/login: Login and get a JWT token
Request body:

json
Copy
{ "email": "email@example.com", "password": "password123" }
GET /api/user/profile: Get user profile (Requires JWT token in Authorization header)
Example header:

bash
Copy
Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN>
